# Input validation & import hardening

Source: **`owasp_access_control_policy.md`**, Phase 2 — **`GoDiveInputSanitization`**, **`DiveFileImportLimits`**, **`CatalogCDNPathValidation`**.

## User text

- Route free text through **`GoDiveInputSanitization`** / existing form helpers (**`DiveSiteFormValidation`**, **`UserProfileStore.sanitizedDan*`**, **`DiveNotesValidation`**, buddy name caps).
- Strip **control characters**; enforce max lengths. Do not invent unbounded `TextField` / import string paths.
- Markup characters in site/notes are OK for SwiftUI **`Text`** — do not treat the app as an HTML sink.

## File import (FIT / UDDF)

- Read via **`DiveFileImportLimits.readCappedFileData`** (size + content magic / `<uddf` check). **Never** trust filename/UTI alone.
- Keep picker UTType allow-lists (**`DiveFileImporterPresentation`**); re-validate content after pick.
- Enforce profile-sample caps and parse deadline in decoders (dive count is uncapped). On UDDF timeout / sample overflow, **abort `XMLParser` immediately** — do not soft-flag and keep parsing. Fail closed with user-facing **`DiveFileImportLimits.Error`** copy.
- UDDF: **`XMLParser.shouldResolveExternalEntities = false`**; reject DTD / `<!ENTITY` in the file prefix.

## Catalog CDN

- Base URL **HTTPS only** (**`CatalogCDNSecretsBootstrap.validatedBaseURL`**).
- Relative paths must pass **`CatalogCDNPathValidation.isAllowedRelativePath`** (`catalog/v1/…`, no `..`).
- Prefer **`CatalogCDNSessionFactory.makeSession`** (same-host HTTPS redirects, response size cap). Keep SHA-256 fail-closed.

## Do not

- Load unbounded `Data(contentsOf:)` for dive imports.
- Allow `http://` CDN bases or open redirects off-host.
- Resolve XML external entities or accept DOCTYPE/entity payloads in UDDF.
